f course in her immediate future precisely what comes next remains to be seen however“you will see me out there” she said “i just don’t know quite where that will be” correction july   an article on wednesday about an announcement by emily k rafferty president of the metropolitan museum of art that she will retire next spring misstated the day of the announcement and of the ensuing speculation in the art world about her working relationship with thomas p campbell the met’s director and chief executive they occurred tuesday not wednesday continue reading the main story we’re interested in your feedback on this page tell us what you think whats next loading go to home page » site index the new york times emily k rafferty executive profile  biography  bloomberg july    am et capital markets company overview of pjt partners inc snapshotpeople  overviewboard memberscommittees executive profile emily k rafferty director pjt partners incagetotal calculated compensationthis person is connected to  board members in  different organizations across  different industriessee board relationships background ms emily k rafferty serves as the president of metropolitan museum of art ms rafferty serves as the chief administrative officer of metropolitan where she is responsible for supervising more than  museum employees in the areas of finance technology and information services legal affairs development membership communications construction and facilities management merchandising government relations human resources and security she serves as an ex officio  member at the museum’s board she has been on the staff of the metropolitan museum since  she began her career at the met as an administrator for corporate foundation and individual fundraising and then served as manager of development from  to  from  to  she served as vice president for development and membership she served as senior vice president of development and membership in  and then to senior vice president for external 