ncial services industry the college fed challenge is a team competition for undergraduates inspired by the working of the federal open market committee the community credit interactive highlights credit conditions including measures of credit inclusion and stress at the national state and county levels emily k rafferty emily kernan rafferty is president emerita of the metropolitan museum of art the nation’s largest and most comprehensive art museum  she was elected president by the metropolitan’s board of trustees in  after a twentynine yearlong career at the institution where she rose through the ranks in the areas of development and external affairs  as the metropolitan’s chief administrative officer she oversaw some  full and parttime museum employees in the areas of finance technology legal affairs development membership communications construction and facilities management merchandising human resources security and government relations at the federal state and city levels  ms rafferty has served on the staff of the metropolitan museum since  she began her career at the met as an administrator for corporate foundation and individual fundraising and then served as manager of development from  through  from  through  she was vice president for development and membership she was promoted to senior vice president for development and membership in  and then to senior vice president for external affairs in  ms rafferty has also served since  as chairwoman of nyc  company the city’s official tourism and marketing agency in addition ms rafferty is a member of the board of directors of the national september  memorial  museum in  she was named to the board of the federal reserve bank of new york she became chairman of the new york fed in december  ms rafferty began her professional career in  as an assistant to david rockefeller jr in boston focusing on his interests in the arts education and philanthropy from  through  she was deputy director of education at bostons institute of contemporary art born and raised in new york city ms rafferty earned her bachelor of arts degree cum laude from boston university in  she received its college of arts  sciences distinguished alumni award the highest honor bestowed upon alumni to recognize extraordinary accomplishments in their professions or communities ms rafferty is a frequent speaker on nonprofit management and fundraising and has long been actively affiliated with a number of arts and intermuseum organizations ms rafferty has been a member since  of arttable board of directors  a member of both the association of fundraising professionals and women in financial development and for ten years served on the development committee of the american association of museums the steering committee of the association for a better new york the women’s forum and media nyc  the recipient of many awards and honors ms rafferty received the honorary degree of doctor of humane letters from pace university in  other honorary degrees have been awarded by fairfield university doctor of laws in  and the college of new rochelle doctor of humane letters in  in  she received the new york university lewis rudin award for exemplary service to new york city  from  through  she has been named one of new york city’s  most influential women by crain’s new york business she was the  honoree of arttable a group of leading women in cultural affairs and has earned both a special service award for the museum from the new york landmarks conservancy and a community and public service “emmy” award from the national academy for television arts and sciences natas    among her many voluntary activities she is a lifetime honorary trustee of the convent of the sacred heart school in new york having served on the board for fifteen years beginning in  and as its chairman from  through  she was also president of the blue hill troupe gilbert and sullivan repertory theater from  to  a group with which she has been affiliated since  she has served for more than ten years as board vice president of the independent school chairmen association   emily rafferty is married to john rafferty a retired audit partner at ernst  young the couple live in manhattan and have a grown son and daughter and two grandchildren june  international services seminars  training services for financial institutions governance  culture reform data visualization economic researchtracker xml data site map for employees only contact us terms of use privacy emily raffertys notsostill life at the metropolitan museum of art  wsj dow jones a news corp companynews corp is a network of leading companies in the worlds of diversified media news education and information servicesdow jonesbarronsbigchartsdjxdow jones newswiresfactivafinancial newsmansion globalmarketwatchnewsplusprivate marketsrisk  compliancewsj conferencewsj prowsj videowsjcomnews corpbig decisionsbusiness spectatorcheckoutharper collinsnew york postproptigerrearealtorcomstoryfulthe australianthe sunthe timessubscribe nowsign inthe wall street journalsearchsearch→ ‘skinny’ repeal of obamacare fails in senate us gdp advanced  in second quarter senators move to block trump from ousting sessions scaramucci erupts over priebus and leakers russia to kick out some us diplomats over sanctions pakistan prime minister removed from office over panama papers amazon’s expansion costs take a toll tax report bad news if you make  to  higher taxes for many an american scourge fentanyl is now stinging law enforcement uber approaches ge ceo jeff immelt about top role cheap eggs flood us grocery stores globalization in retreat china’s next target us microchip hegemony the ahed spain has a debt problem and so now it has a zorro problem breaking news us economic growth accelerated to  rate in second quarter on solid spending by consumers businesses facebook twitter small medium large save article sign in to save subscribe to wsj urban gardner emily raffertys notsostill life at the metro